5.13   We recommended and the Management agreed that the:
ICO-Municipal Accountant to exert his best efforts to gather documents relative to the fund transfers for identification of source agencies and the status of balances;
ICO-Municipal Accountant to prepare the corresponding aging of Due to NGAs, GOCCs and LGUs accounts and present the same in the Notes to Financial Statements;
ICO-Municipal Accountant to reclassify the donation of ECCD and DOH from the Due to NGAs account to the Government Equity account;
Municipal Treasurer to refund the unused balances with identified source agencies, or seek their written approval that the balance may be utilized for other certain purposes; and
Concerned Municipal officials to effect the implementation of projects under the trust fund for the purpose they were established.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to:

Strengthen the implementation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan by monitoring periodically all the programs, projects and activities and taking note of reported deviations;
Strictly require complete submission of the reports from the barangays and verify the existence of the traditional practices based on the reports submitted;
Provide trainings to the households on the proper management of solid wastes and extend the information, education and communication campaign.
Lastly, the LGU through the MSWMB should pursue a comprehensive final disposal facility.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year as basis of setting up the RPT/SET Receivables prescribed by the said manual;
Officer In-Charge (OIC) - Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjustments so that the amounts of RPT/SET Receivables would harmonize with that of the Deferred Real Property

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to:

Strengthen the implementation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan by monitoring periodically all the programs, projects and activities and taking note of reported deviations;
