Provide trainings to the households on the proper management of solid wastes and extend the information, education and communication campaign.
Lastly, the LGU through the MSWMB should pursue a comprehensive final disposal facility.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year as basis of setting up the RPT/SET Receivables prescribed by the said manual;
Officer In-Charge (OIC) - Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjustments so that the amounts of RPT/SET Receivables would harmonize with that of the Deferred Real Property Tax Income and Deferred Special Tax Income. Moreover, monitoring of the collections and updating of the records should be done dutifully.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to:

Strengthen the implementation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan by monitoring periodically all the programs, projects and activities and taking note of reported deviations;

Strictly require complete submission of the reports from the barangays and verify the existence of the traditional practices based on the reports submitted;

Provide trainings to the households on the proper management of solid wastes and extend the information, education and communication campaign.

Lastly, the LGU through the MSWMB should pursue a comprehensive final disposal facility.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Enter into a MOA with the barangays requiring them liquidation reports for similar fund transfers as a requirement provided under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations. This maybe be included in the resolution passed by the Sangguniang Bayan relative to fund transfers to barangays;

Instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to reclassify the said fund transfers from Subsidy to Other Local Government Units to Due from other LGUs

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board to:
Strengthen the implementation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Plan by monitoring periodically all the programs, projects and activities and taking note of reported deviations;
Strictly require complete submission of the reports from the barangays and verify the existence of the traditional practices based on the reports submitted;
Provide trainings to the households on the proper management of solid wastes and extend the information, education and communication campaign.
Lastly, the LGU through the MSWMB should pursue a comprehensive final disposal facility.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Enter into a MOA with the barangays requiring them liquidation reports for similar fund transfers as a requirement provided under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations. This maybe be included in the resolution passed by the Sangguniang Bayan relative to fund transfers to barangays;
Instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to reclassify the said fund transfers from Subsidy to Other Local Government Units to Due from other LGUs;
Direct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to monitor and demand the liquidation reports from the recipient LGUs.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive direct the Inventory Committee to:

Conduct the annual physical count of all the property, plant and equipment owned by the Municipality;
Prepare promptly the Report on the Physical Count of PPE;
Submit religiously the RPCPPE to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year.



We also recommend that the Accountant maintain the prescribed PPELC and reconcile it with the RPCPPE to establish the correct amount of the PPE in the financial statements.
